Harold E. West was a British rower who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics.
West was a member of Thames Rowing Club. In 1928 he was a member of the first eight, which won the Grand Challenge Cup at Henley Royal Regatta and then represented Great Britain rowing at the 1928 Summer Olympics.
